<i>interjection</i>: 에헴 [에헴], 어험 [어험], 아 [아] <i>noun</i>: 큰기침 [큰기침] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>interjection</i><br>
<dt>에헴 [에헴]</dt><br>
<dd>ahem; ehem</dd><br>
<dd>점잖은 체하거나 사람이 있음을 알리려고 일부러 내는 큰기침 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>A coughing sound made intentionally by the speaker to pretend to be decent or let others sense his/her presence.</dd><br>
<dt>어험 [어험]</dt><br>
<dd>1. ahem</dd><br>
<dd>위엄 있게 기침하는 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation uttered when the speaker coughs in a dignified manner.</dd><br>
<dd>2. ahem</dd><br>
<dd>기척을 나타내려고 일부러 내는 기침 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>A coughing sound made intentionally by the speaker to let others sense his/her presence.</dd><br>
<dt>아 [아]</dt><br>
<dd>1. oh; ah</dd><br>
<dd>놀라움, 당황함, 초조함, 다급함의 느낌을 나타낼 때 내는 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation uttered when the speaker expresses his/her surprise, embarrassment, impatience, or urgency.</dd><br>
<dd>2. oh; wow; ah</dd><br>
<dd>기쁨이나 감동의 느낌을 나타낼 때 내는 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation uttered when the speaker expresses his/her delight or excitement.</dd><br>
<dd>3. oh; aww; oh no</dd><br>
<dd>걱정, 근심, 안타까움, 한탄의 느낌을 나타낼 때 내는 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation uttered when the speaker expresses the feelings of worry, anxiety, regret, or lamentation.</dd><br>
<dd>4. umm; ahem</dd><br>
<dd>남에게 말을 걸거나 주의를 끌 때, 말에 앞서 내는 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation uttered before the speaker begins his/her words when he/she talks to someone or attracts someone's attention.</dd><br>
<dd>5. oh; aha; oh yeah</dd><br>
<dd>모르던 것을 깨달았음을 나타낼 때 내는 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation uttered when the speaker realizes something he/she did not know.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>큰기침 [큰기침]</dt><br>
<dd>clearing one's throat; ahem</dd><br>
<dd>위엄을 나타내거나 마음을 가다듬기 위해 큰 소리로 기침함. 또는 그런 기침.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making a coughing sound intentionally to show one's dignity or to calm oneself down, or such a sound.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>